    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith ui2 enabled, switching tabpages while displaying a multi-line message (without entering the pager) results in issues as described below.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nrequire(\"vim._extui\").enable { enable = true }\nvim.cmd.tabnew()\nvim.defer_fn(function()\n  vim.api.nvim_input \":hi<CR>gt\"\nend, 100)\n```\n\nMessage remains shown in the other tabpage, and moving the cursor doesn't dismiss it.\n\nPressing `g<` to open the pager in this state (or just clearing the screen via `<C-L>`) clears the message, but the command-line area remains expanded:\n\n<img width=\"1365\" height=\"664\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/00c098ec-41c6-4741-b371-9b936b739bca\" />\n\nEntering the command-line fixes it (and allows the message to be dismissed again), but the statusline remains blank afterwards.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nMessage is properly dismissed, statusline is shown again.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2162+g1906da52db\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 43 Workstation\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.2.3, tmux 3.5a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nSource",
